"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5392981-2024-04-05-mls-usmnt-olympics-watchlist\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympics    This year's Copa Am\\u00e9rica will be closely watched, but the ensuingOlympic Games in Pariswill have just as much to say about the broader state of the U.S. men's player pool.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 160, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.561838649325588e-35, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the women's side of the Olympic tournament, the men's competition relies on players under the age of 23, though every team is allowed to bring up to three over-age players in the 18-man squad.\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 215, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Handball_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9987949488694181, \"rank\": 0.0012045467680081446, \"text\": \"Olympic tournament\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Handball_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Handball_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  If the team that U.S. Olympic coach Marko Mitrovi\\u0107 selects comes close to matching the program-best 4th place finish in 2000, it would be a potential indicator that the U.S. can now consistently produce top-end talent.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the U.S. is embarrassedin Group A, though, some will fear that 2026 will be the program's high point for quite some time.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the draw in March, Mitrovi\\u0107 touted a \\\"big pool of players that we are following\\\" for potential inclusion.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stressed that he wants to bring \\\"the best 18 players\\\" he can, and did not show his hand yet about areas where he feels he can sacrifice depth given the squad limitations of an Olympic tournament.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 1055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GO DEEPER  USMNT to play France in Olympic tourney opener  With that in mind, here's a crib sheet of Olympic-eligible players to track in the coming months.\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1942723008658905e-17, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This list focuses onMLSplayers, and with good reason: A full half of the most recent Olympic squad currently plays in MLS, and a majority of the rest were developed in MLS academies before moving abroad.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}, {\"begin\": 1382, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Players who have been called in by Mitrovi\\u0107 for the U-23 camps in November and March are designated with an asterisk (*) upon first mention.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.8116625123897024, \"rank\": 0.11369509043931326, \"text\": \"Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gabriel \\\"Gaga\\\" Slonina*has been the senior U.S. team's \\\"goalkeeper of the future\\\" for a couple of years now, and he will not turn 20 until May 15.\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7667491168745194e-25, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's widely expected that he will be one of the two goalkeepers taken to the 2024 Olympics, which would leave one place available for the rest of the pool.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If USMNT head coach Gregg Berhalter decides Slonina would benefit froma place on the Copa Am\\u00e9rica roster, however, it would open the door for a second.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USMNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\", \"score\": 0.9992718947465502, \"rank\": 0.0007286357766396113, \"text\": \"Gregg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Either way, the fight for those one (or two) spots is arguably the closest competition in the entire pool of age-eligible players.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from Slonina, three Olympic-eligible domestic goalkeepers are the top option for an MLS club.\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two led their teams to top honors in 2023, withRoman CelentanoandPatrick Schulte*winning the Supporters' Shield with FC Cincinnati and MLS Cup with the Columbus Crew, respectively.The other goalkeeper in contention isChris Brady*, a Chicago Fire homegrown who inherited the club's starting spot after Slonina, another academy product, left for Chelsea after the 2022 season.\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2342, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supporters'_Shield\", \"score\": 0.9999999947949618, \"rank\": 5.204996840131882e-09, \"text\": \"Supporters' Shield\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supporters'_Shield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supporters'_Shield\"}, {\"begin\": 2366, \"end\": 2379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Cincinnati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.422637669961238e-72, \"text\": \"FC Cincinnati\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Cincinnati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Cincinnati\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MLS_Cup\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.581150642884378e-14, \"text\": \"MLS Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MLS_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MLS_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7504375190727637e-46, \"text\": \"Columbus Crew\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\"}, {\"begin\": 2593, \"end\": 2600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.877314735820055e-17, \"text\": \"Chelsea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their numbers tell an interesting story.\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Celentano holds an edge over his peers on numbers, but it's difficult to separate a goalkeeper's performance from that of the line in front of him, and Celentano benefited from playing behind one of MLS's best defenses in Cincy.\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2868, \"end\": 2871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brady's goal prevention rate of 5.6% has him in the middle of this group, but that work looks borderline Herculean when compared to his backup (Spencer Richey), who has a -19.9% rate across 8 starts since the beginning of last season.\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3042, \"end\": 3056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Richey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spencer Richey\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Richey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Richey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  While Celentano's goal prevention rate looks far better than Brady's or Schulte's, that's relative.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3221, \"end\": 3228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"score\": 0.914506346413508, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schulte\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Celentano ranked 15th among 36 eligible MLS goalkeepers in the stat last season, with Brady in 17th and Schulte in 22nd.\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3289, \"end\": 3292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}, {\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"score\": 0.914506346413508, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schulte\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The difference between this trio is relatively negligible given a range that ran from -20% to +50% league-wide.\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The three are also utilized very differently by each of their teams, which shows up in the non-shot-stopping metrics as well as the eye test.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 2023 began, Schulte's raw passing numbers jump off the page: a 75.6% completion rate that's 9.9% better than Celentano (65.7%) and 13.1% ahead of Brady (62.5%).\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3646, \"end\": 3653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"score\": 0.914506346413508, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schulte\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then again, the Crew goalkeeper plays far fewer long passes, which makes sense given Columbus's possession-heavy style under Wilfried Nancy.\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3880, \"end\": 3888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.244367766038048e-54, \"text\": \"Columbus\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbus_Crew\"}, {\"begin\": 3920, \"end\": 3934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilfried_Nancy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilfried Nancy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilfried_Nancy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilfried_Nancy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brady takes top marks in commanding his area, stifling more crosses than the others.\", \"from\": 3936, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Considering shot-stopping, distribution and sweeping altogether, Brady appears to have a narrow edge as the top option of this trio.\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next couple of months will be crucial for Schulte, who was a revelation last fall but needs to display better consistency between the posts.\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4201, \"end\": 4208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"score\": 0.914506346413508, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schulte\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schulte,_Kansas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If he can not, Celentano stands out as a shot-stopping specialist - arguably, he's been in the best form of this trio, if not any MLS goalkeeper, through the season's early weeks.\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4430, \"end\": 4433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six defenders have viable cases for the Olympic roster.\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Conveniently for our purposes, they are divided evenly between left back, right back, and center back.\", \"from\": 4537, \"to\": 4639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At left back,John Tolkin*andCaleb Wiley*have been regulars in this squad, and will likely soon compete to be Antonee Robinson's main backup for the senior team.\", \"from\": 4641, \"to\": 4801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4654, \"end\": 4665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tolkin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Tolkin\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tolkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tolkin\"}, {\"begin\": 4750, \"end\": 4766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonee_Robinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Antonee Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonee_Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonee_Robinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiley is a regular for Atlanta United at 19 years old, and his ability to play further afield on the wing is valuable for the constraints of an 18-man squad.\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 4959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4802, \"end\": 4807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\", \"score\": 0.999999999908141, \"rank\": 9.085860831314211e-11, \"text\": \"Wiley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\"}, {\"begin\": 4825, \"end\": 4839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlanta United\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tolkin, 21, is arguably the best left back in MLS and appears ready to take the next step with a move abroad.\", \"from\": 4960, \"to\": 5069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5006, \"end\": 5009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At right back,Nathan Harriel*is a regular selection by Mitrovi\\u0107.\", \"from\": 5073, \"to\": 5137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5128, \"end\": 5136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.8116625123897024, \"rank\": 0.11369509043931326, \"text\": \"Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another Union academy product, Harriel leads all MLS right backs with 6.07 interceptions and blocked passes per 1,000 opposing touches -\\u00a0a massive impact even when weighted for possession.\", \"from\": 5138, \"to\": 5326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5187, \"end\": 5190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also boasts a 56.3% duel win rate, making him a tricky mark to overcome for onrushing wingers.\", \"from\": 5327, \"to\": 5424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Sporting KC'sJake Davisis finally getting his due this season after a breakout 2023, and for good reason.\", \"from\": 5426, \"to\": 5546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No MLS right back averages more 'true' tackles -\\u00a0tackles, plus times that a defender is bounced off the ball carrier, as well fouls committed -\\u00a0per 1,000 opposing touches than Davis' rate of 8.76.\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5550, \"end\": 5553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2898712724978287e-38, \"text\": \"MLS\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Soccer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That ballhawk mentality has been vital to Sporting Kansas City and could play very well in an Olympic tournament.\", \"from\": 5744, \"to\": 5857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5795, \"end\": 5806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sporting_Kansas_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6173279793522757e-24, \"text\": \"Kansas City\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sporting_Kansas_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sporting_Kansas_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has yet to be called in by Mitrovi\\u0107, however, and his emergence may have come slightly too late in the cycle to make this squad.\", \"from\": 5858, \"to\": 5989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5888, \"end\": 5896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.8116625123897024, \"rank\": 0.11369509043931326, \"text\": \"Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's a shame in my book.\", \"from\": 5990, \"to\": 6016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GO DEEPER  How Jake Davis supplanted Graham Zusi as Sporting KC's right back  At the heart of defense,George Campbell*has benefitted mightily since being traded from Atlanta United to CF Montr\\u00e9al after the 2022 season.\", \"from\": 6018, \"to\": 6236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6033, \"end\": 6037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"score\": 0.7217259032021138, \"rank\": 0.3855128831017742, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\"}, {\"begin\": 6055, \"end\": 6066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Graham_Zusi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Graham Zusi\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Graham_Zusi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Graham_Zusi\"}, {\"begin\": 6120, \"end\": 6135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Ashley_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4702273788772678e-24, \"text\": \"George Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Ashley_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Ashley_Campbell\"}, {\"begin\": 6184, \"end\": 6198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlanta United\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_United_FC\"}, {\"begin\": 6202, \"end\": 6213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CF Montr\\u00e9al\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has become a dependable starter who likes to converge on attackers before the ball gets to the box.\", \"from\": 6237, \"to\": 6339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That mindset shows in the data, too: although his 48.4% aerial rate is very poor for the position, his 11.71 ball recoveries per 1,000 opposing touches is among the league's best.\", \"from\": 6340, \"to\": 6519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Davis,Jalen Nealhas yet to play under Mitrovi\\u0107.\", \"from\": 6521, \"to\": 6573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6564, \"end\": 6572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandar_Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.8116625123897024, \"rank\": 0.11369509043931326, \"text\": \"Mitrovi\\u0107\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", 